title: Kalonzo launches search for his look-alike after Twitter frenzy - Nairobi News
text:
Wiper leader Kalonzo Musyoka has waded into a debate on social media over a picture of a man with striking resemblance to the former vice president. 
Mr Musyoka was however quick to declare that the young man is “not my work”. 
Speaking in Embu town on Thursday, the Cord co-principal said he was equally surprised by his resemblance to the man from Kiambu county only known as Kinyanjui. 
The picture of Mr Musyoka’s look-alike went viral on Twitter under the hashtag #KalonzoBro. 
“I have seen another Kalonzo in the internet. Huyo kijana wa Kiambu anaitwa Kinyanjui ni Kalonzo kabisa. Ni Kalonzo tupu. When you see him you’ll think that he is like my true copy. He is my complete look-alike. But be assure that I didn’t sire him,” he said. 
Mr Musyoka said he would be looking for the man so they can get acquainted. 
He was accompanied by Ford Kenya leader Moses Wetangula. Latest Stories
